<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 22 at 3:23AM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED RISK OF WILDFIRE SPREAD TODAY...
Northwesterly winds gusting to 25 to 35 mph will combine with
relative humidities dropping below 30 percent this afternoon to
produce an elevated risk of fire spread today for northwest
Connecticut and the Berkshires of western Massachusetts.
Open burning is not recommended today. Follow instructions of
local fire wardens. Be careful when handling and disposing of
ignition sources outdoors, such as cigarettes or matches.</description>
